The Marzhauser TANGO family of controllers can be controlled using the [[Ludl | Ludl adapter]]. It is tested using the Tango-DT with serial interface. The Tango-PCI and Tango-DT were also tested on Windows using the USB interface. To configure Micro-Manager to work with the Marzhauser Tango you need to do the following:
<table><tr><td>
<tr><td>1.</td><td>Install the TANGO and verify that it works.</td></tr>
<tr><td>2.</td><td>Switch TANGO to Ludl MAC5000 compatible mode.</td></tr>
<tr><td>3.</td><td>Download the MMConfig_Tango.cfg example configuration file and use it in Micro-Manager.</td></tr>
</table>

